Rating: 4
A great recipe to begin with, however, I like to make this dish with chicken and a few extras to liven the flavor! After sauteing the garlic, I also add about a 1/2 cup of white wine and 1/4 cup of lemon juice and let it cook down to about half. Then I cook about 3-4 chicken breasts in a separate pan, cut it up after it's cooked and then add it to the tomato mixture at the end. It's one of my husband's favorites!

